place_info.title: Cafe Niloufer Premium Lounge - Banjara Hills
place_info.address: Divine Banjara - AMN, 8-2-685/P2 & P3, Road No. 12, Venkateswara Colony, Banjara Hills, Hyderabad, Telangana 500034, India

reviews.snippet:
Cafe Niloufer: A Bustling, Multi-Level Experience
Cafe Niloufer is a three-storied establishment known for its heavy crowds on both the ground and first floors, suggesting a lively, non-premium atmosphere in these areas. For those seeking a more peaceful experience, the cafe offers a second-floor premium section with an hourly charge and minimum billing.
While it might not be ideal for a quiet retreat due to its busy, buzzing, and "most happening" ambiance, it's an excellent choice if you enjoy a vibrant and energetic environment. The cafe is highly regarded for its good food and a wide, continuously upgrading variety of options, contributing to an overall nice experience.

reviews.snippet:
We there there for an art exhibition at CCT Spaces and this was the only outlet closest to the venue. Got addicted to Maska Bun. Nilofar’s tea had unique taste. I also tried some snacks. + Samosas. This is surprisingly a vegetarian only restaurant. Ambience was amazing, huge set up and lot of room to go around.

The owner of Cafe Niloufer in Hyderabad is A. Babu Rao, and his son, Shashank, also plays a significant role in the business. Babu Rao started the cafe in 1978 with a vision to create a chai that embodies the spirit of Hyderabad

reviews.snippet: Cafe Niloufer is huge and has a very gd variety of food..their seating is big and very spacious and  you have your privacy..its a multicuisine restaurant and i loved the food .Everything was good except one thing which was a complete shocker that comes in the end..when we asked for water they served it in small disposable bottles instead of a glass..when we asked for the bill we noticed that they hv charged us for water served and it was a ridiculous amount. Firstly water is the first thing that anyone serves in a restaurant and if they were going to charge for it they should have mentioned  it right in the beginning. The waiters always ask if we would like to have bottled water or regular water and then the customer is free to choose. But that was not the case here. It felt very cheap that something like this can happen to you in a high-end restaurant. I felt very let down as I had to pay for something that I was not told about and dint ask for..it's just about being upfront about it because it left a bad taste n experience..

reviews.snippet:
Paying Rs.100 for a tiny cup of tea? Hurts. Hurts in places you didn’t even know existed. 😜

But then again… Hyderabadi hokar agar Niloufer ki Irani chai nahi pi, toh kya kiya miya?

When you’re craving chai vibes but also battling open pores and the heat like a skincare warrior, this one’s a solid win. 😅

The crowd? Basically a Charminar branch copy-paste.
But the vibe and ambience? Total 4-star.

reviews.snippet:
Honestly this place is the most overhyped place of Hyderabad, the special tea costs 150₹ and special coffee costs 120₹. Nothing worth the price.
No service as it has self service but before you get the order the service is bit messy, no one knows what they are attending to serve the correct order in less time.
About special tea, nothing was special in it, i'd prefer ordinary tapri tea than this.
About special coffee ufff it was just a Nescafe nothing else, nothing special in it, so better visit any cafe to have your coffee, atleast you can enjoy the service and ambience with quality of coffee.
Bun maska, if you have eaten the bun maska in Pune then please do not try this as it is not up to the mark.
Yeah the only thing I love was Rasmalai pastry, it was at 140₹ but yeah it was totally worth the price and the taste was delicious.

- ₹ahul Mo₹e

reviews.snippet:
⭐⭐⭐⭐

A Delightful Experience with a Few Hiccups

I recently visited Niloufer Cafe and had a mostly positive experience with a variety of items:

- Tea: Simply amazing! One of the best teas I've had in a long time.
- Bun Maska: Absolutely fantastic. The bun was incredibly soft, and the butter was perfectly balanced!
- Vada Pav: Wonderful. It made me feel like I was in Mumbai or Pune.
- Tarri Poha: A bit disappointing. It lacked flavor, and I had to add extra salt. It didn't quite live up to the taste of Nagpur's Tarri Poha.
- Belgian Chocolate Croissant: It was good, but not as authentic as a European croissant.
- Osmania Biscuits: Excellent. They melt in your mouth seamlessly.
- Tawa Pulao with Raita: Decent enough.

Overall, Niloufer Cafe offers a delightful experience with a few areas for improvement. It's a great place to enjoy a variety of dishes and beverages, with some items standing out more than others. I highly recommend trying their tea and Osmania biscuits!

reviews.snippet:
Went to Café Niloufer a few days back, and man, that place was packed even at 11:30 pm. Had to wait a bit before snagging a spot upstairs. Downstairs was crazy busy, no room to move. Good thing they had valet parking.

Now, about the food. Tried their special chai, and it was awesome. Lemon tea was a hit with my friends and family – they couldn't stop talking about it.

But let me tell you about the real star – the Bun Maska. It was crazy good – soft, warm, and a bit sweet. We started with two, but couldn't resist and ordered a couple more to eat there and a couple to take away.

We also tried the Poha, but honestly, it was a bit plain on its own, no salt at all. But when you mix it with that side gravy thing, it becomes delicious.

Overall, dealing with the crowd was worth it for those buns and chai. Café Niloufer, you got a fan in me.

reviews.snippet: Visited  with high expectations and tried their Niloufer Special Tea with bun maska. The tea was disappointingly too sweet, but the bun maska was soft, fluffy, and delicious. The menu offers a wide range of options, including tea, coffee, pastries, cakes, and snacks like vada pav, sabudana, subway, and Chinese dishes. However, the overall experience was a 3/5. The mismanagement at the beverages service counter, with no proper queue and chaotic service, detracted from the experience, despite the good ambience. Do visit and share your thoughts!

reviews.snippet:
I had the absolute pleasure of dining at Cafe Niloufer Premium Lounge in Banjara Hills, and without a doubt, it deserves nothing less than a perfect 5/5 rating.

The Irani chai at this establishment is a true masterpiece. Its aroma alone is enough to enchant the senses, and the taste is nothing short of exceptional. Paired with the bun masala, it was a delightful journey through a world of rich, sweet, and savory flavors.

The onion rings were a revelation in the world of fried treats – golden and crispy on the outside, tender and flavorful on the inside. A perfect appetizer that set the bar high.

The dragon chili mushrooms were an explosion of flavors, offering just the right amount of spice and a texture that was both crispy and succulent. It's a dish that keeps you coming back for more.

As for the spaghetti aglio e olio, it was a beautiful example of the elegance of simplicity. The pasta was cooked to perfection, and the garlic-infused oil added a heavenly dimension to the dish. It was a taste sensation that I won't soon forget.

Cafe Niloufer Premium Lounge goes beyond just serving food; it offers an unforgettable experience. The service was impeccable, and the lounge's ambiance was both upscale and inviting. For any food enthusiast, this place is a hidden gem that deserves to be explored. I can't recommend it highly enough, and I'm already looking forward to my next visit to savor these exquisite dishes once again. A resounding 5/5 rating is well-deserved!
